The Shell Petroleum Development Company of Nigeria Limited has completed the process for sales of its 30 per cent interest in Oil Mining Lease 17 in the Eastern Niger Delta and associated infrastructure to TNOG Oil and Gas Limited for $533m. Shell said it has received approvals from the relevant authorities of the Federal Government of Nigeria to complete the process. According to the statement, TNOG Oil and Gas is a related company of Heirs Holdings Limited and Transnational Corporation of Nigeria Plc. “A total of $453m was paid at completion with the balance to be paid over an agreed period. SPDC will retain its interest in the Port Harcourt Industrial and Residential Areas, which fall within the lease area,” the SPDC said. Details shortly…